# Negate multiplicity (analysis sec 4.5 R9, Q5): one negated key A gates
# several pred rows (A,B*). Gaining seen(A) must retract EVERY (A,B) row;
# losing it must re-derive them all.
#
# Batch 1: feed (1,10),(1,11),(1,12) [key 1, three rows] and (2,20) [key 2].
#          No block. out = {(1,10),(1,11),(1,12),(2,20)}.
# Batch 2: block 1. All three key-1 rows die; key 2 survives.
#          out = {(2,20)}.  (three `-` crossover folds)
# Batch 3: unblock 1. All three key-1 rows re-derived.
#          out = {(1,10),(1,11),(1,12),(2,20)}.  (three `+` crossover folds)
batch
+ feed 1 10
+ feed 1 11
+ feed 1 12
+ feed 2 20
end

batch
+ block 1
end

batch
- block 1
end
